      • processSamples

        public void processSamples(TimelineCursor timeCursor,
                  int sampleCount,
                  SampleOpcode opcode,
                  Object value)
        Process sampleCount sequential samples with identical values. sampleCount will usually be 1, but may be larger than 1. Implementors may just loop processing identical values, but some implementations may optimize adding a bunch of repeated values
        Specified by:
        processSamples in interface SampleProcessor
        Parameters:
        timeCursor - a TimeCursor instance, which supplies successive int UNIX times
        sampleCount - the count of sequential, identical values
        opcode - the opcode of the sample value, which may not be a REPEAT opcode
        value - the value of this kind of sample over the sampleCount samples
